definitions.definition: An event that appears inexplicable by the laws of nature and so is held to be supernatural in origin.
examples: Many religious beliefs are based on miracles .
An example of a miracle associated with Muhammad is the splitting of the moon.

definitions.definition: A fortunate outcome that prevails despite overwhelming odds against it.
An awesome and exceptional example of something.
